parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Crankshaft Breakage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The breakage of the crankshaft can cause the engine to shut down suddenly, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the temperature and directional gauges can lead to a lack of critical information for the driver, potentially causing accidents or other safety issues.
Sudden unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to accelerate out of control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without input from the driver
the accelerator pedal becomes stuck or stuck in a position
the vehicle fails to respond to braking input

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty courtesy lamp switch can cause the courtesy lamp to stay on, draining the battery and potentially leading to electrical system failures or fires.
symptoms: The courtesy lamp stays on and cannot be turned off
the vehicle's electrical system is malfunctioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tire Failure and Loss of Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden tire failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds. The resulting damage can be costly and time-consuming to repair.
Tire tread separation can lead to loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds. The resulting damage can be costly and time-consuming to repair.
